FBIS4-42045 "drsov126_m_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-126 Daily Report 30 Jun 1994 Tajikistan Aid Convoy Reaches Badakhshan Aid Convoy Reaches Badakhshan LD3006100294 Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network in Tajik 0500 GMT 30 Jun 94 LD3006100294 Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network Tajik BFN [Text] A large truck convoy carrying food arrived in Badakhshan Autonomous Oblast yesterday. The convoy was carrying essential goods, including 210 tonnes of flour. The Khorog city bakery, which had been unable to work for nearly a week, resumed bread production. The convoy also brought [word indistinct], fuel oil, other foodstuffs, and industrial goods. The convoy was escorted by troops to the western approaches of Pamir. It was not felt necessary for the troops to escort the convoy in the territory of Badakhshan Autonomous Oblast. The tanks and armored vehicles accompanying the convoy form Dushanbe stopped at the Saghirdasht Pass. The convoy reached its destination without any hindrance.
